Deathchase <span style="font-style: italic">was</span> great in its day. More remarkably, it was all crammed into 16K - probably one of the last great 16K games, along with Jet Pac.<br /><br />Jet Set Willy I could kind of go along with... it was quite a remarkable game for its time, but too hard as well as being - infamously - impossible to complete because of the notorious &quot;Attic Bug&quot;, which had to be remedied with a POKE.  <br /><br />I think it was the hundreds of POKEs for JSW that vastly increased its longevity. Playing it with just the seven lives was dull by comparison, and usually made for a very short game...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=76">Cultured_Janner</a> — Fri Jul 22, 2011 3:24 am</p><hr />
